            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1587400178267-1637683377755-x1500.jpeg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs, then add 225ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> of the <strong>single soya </strong>(save the rest for later!) and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add the <strong>cracked black pepper </strong>with the <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and half <span class=\"text-danger\">[all]</span> of the <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat, then add any <strong>resting juices</strong> from the plate with the steaks and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>dairy-free peppercorn sauce</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 2? Save the remaining mustard for another meal!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1641298205063-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1641298205063-x400.jpg",
